    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the CFD hemolysis model for the VAD COU based on the completed validation results showing NIH predictions within combined uncertainty at 4 of 5 operating points, and Monte Carlo UQ demonstrating 95th-percentile NIH below the clinical threshold. Six credibility factors remain at achieved level 1 and are flagged as epistemic gaps; however, the team judged the overall evidence sufficient for the intended low-assurance decision. The stale blood rheology dataset (vintage 2018) was noted in the model inputs factor but was not identified as a barrier to acceptance, and no re-validation against the 2026 model revision was required by the review process.",
